{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-jsx","path":"/how-to-check-out-a-remote-git-branch","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2 id=\"how-to-check-out-a-remote-git-branch\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#how-to-check-out-a-remote-git-branch\" aria-label=\"how to check out a remote git branch permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How to check out a remote Git branch</h2>\n<p>You need to work on a git branch that you don't have locally, but you are not sure how to pull and switch to that branch.\nLet's first list the remote branches so we are sure the branch exists. To list all of the remote branches run:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">git</span> branch -a</code></pre></div>\n<p>This will list all of the local and remote branches. </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">local_branch1\nlocal_branch2\nremotes/new_branch</code></pre></div>\n<p>The first displayed are all local branches, and the branches that contain <code class=\"language-text\">remote/</code> are the remote branches.\nCopy the name of the remote branch you want to work on and execute:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">git</span> checkout new_branch</code></pre></div>\n<p>You should see the <code class=\"language-text\">Branch &#39;new_branch&#39; set up to track remote branch &#39;new_branch&#39; from &#39;origin&#39;.</code> message. This means you have successfully checkout to the  <code class=\"language-text\">new_branch</code>. </p>\n<h2 id=\"multiple-remotes\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#multiple-remotes\" aria-label=\"multiple remotes permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Multiple remotes</h2>\n<p>There are cases where the repository will contain more than one remote. In that case run:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">git</span> checkout -t <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>name of remote<span class=\"token operator\">></span>/new_branch</code></pre></div>","timeToRead":1,"excerpt":"How to check out a remote Git branch You need to work on a git branch that you don't have locally, but you are not sure how to pull and…","frontmatter":{"title":"How to check out a remote Git branch","date":"2020-05-20 23:53:42 +0200","categories":["git"],"tags":["git","git-remote","git-checkout","git-branches"],"description":null,"keywords":"git, git-remote, git-checkout, git-branches","author":"Zoran Pandovski","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":204,"height":132,"src":"/static/b6e56d11b55e08f4d1541cb522313a8b/02521/git.png","srcSet":"/static/b6e56d11b55e08f4d1541cb522313a8b/02521/git.png 1x"}}}},"fields":{"slug":"/how-to-check-out-a-remote-git-branch","date":"2020-05-20T21:53:42.000Z"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/how-to-check-out-a-remote-git-branch","nexttitle":"How to reset the MySQL root password","nextslug":"/how-to-reset-the-mysql-root-password","prevtitle":"How to list `dot` files in Linux","prevslug":"/how-to-list-dot-files-in-linux","tagList":["python","pandas","abstraction","OOP","Class","java","collection","API","Map","HashMap","LinkedHashMap","TreeMap","Python","cli","args","argparse","javascript","es6","beginner","codenewbie","Primary_key","implementation","Composite_key","language-support","localization","internationalization","linux","file permissions","Project Euler","Algortithms","SQL","database","commands","GO","Datatypes","Variables","Constants","HTML5","Web development","tricks","NumpPy","array","NLP","libraries","text processing","go","golang","data-structure","optimization","java 7","Java 8","comparison","mkdir(make-dir) and rmdir(remove-dir command) command","nodejs","backend","frontend","postgres","mac","installation","games","gamedev","memory","html","bootstrap","web development","data","strings","final","finally","finalize","Git","GitLens","VS Code Extension","CSS","Images","Image Display","CSS Variables","JavaScript","sort","localeCompare","Responsive Fonts","CSS Fonts","interface","default method","static static","plot","spring boot","controller","annotation","mvc","rest","random","List","Set","Queue","hacktoberfest","python3","features","set","hashset","treeset","linkedhashset","list","array list","linked list","vector","slice","delete","one-liner","string","input-stream","nan","infinity","positive-infinity","negative-infinity","ci","travis-ci","travis","type-error","dict","pypi","pypi-stats","modules","python-modules","python-with","with statement","tags","doctype","meta","viewport","meta-tag","git","git-write","git pull","lists","list-index","dictionaries","dict-keys","current-time","millis","milliseconds","c-shar